gomodel:SYNGO_798  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1 shows enriched binding of P2X ligands to purified synaptosomes indicating synaptic localization. Figure 3A highlights how this synaptic associated receptor distributes across synaptic sub-compartments. Synaptosomes differentially detergent extracted to give presynaptic (pre), postsynaptic (post) and neuronal active zone (NAZ) show an enriched post-synaptic association of P2X-1 in pH 8 detergent insoluble fraction (post). Further, figure 3 shows selective staining with same P2X-1 selective antibody on intact synaptosomes immobilized on glass. (Antibodies quality controlled by Alamone).\n\n30/10/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and methods: Male Wistar rats (8 weeks)......" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_798" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

